HEADWORD: Triarian
<hw>Tri*a"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triarii</ets>, <ets>pl</ets>., a class of Roman soldiers who formed
the third rank from the front, fr. <ets>tres</ets>, <ets>tria</ets>,
three.]</ety> <def>Occupying the third post or rank.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

